      <title type="html">Configure SSH</title>
      <link href="https://www.briglamoreaux.com/2011/09/30/configure-ssh.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Configure SSH" />
      <published>2011-09-30T00:00:00+00:00</published>
      <updated>2011-09-30T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
      <id>https://www.briglamoreaux.com/2011/09/30/configure-ssh</id>
      <content type="html" xml:base="https://www.briglamoreaux.com/2011/09/30/configure-ssh.html">&lt;p&gt;I recently set up a few new servers and needed to allow other developers access. Here is how I did it:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Add new user&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;sudo adduser bbdiddle&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Add user to sudoers&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;`sudo vi /etc/sudoers&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;# Add this line to the sodoers file bbdiddle ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL`&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Enable ssh&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;`sudo vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;# Change to yes to allow ssh PasswordAuthentication yes`&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Restart ssh&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;`sudo /etc/init.d/ssh restart&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;# Redhat sudo service sshd restart`&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</content>

      
      
      
      
      

